section
  markdown:
    ## Basics [#](#basics)
    {: #basics}

    There is only one thing required to give anchers and buttns *button* styling:

    {: .pco-demo-list}
    * Add the class `btn` to your element

  =code_sample
    a.btn href="#" Click Me!

  markdown:
    You may then use modifying classes to change the characteristics of your button:

  =code_sample
    a.btn.btn--danger href="#" WARNING!

  markdown:
    Disabling a button with the `disabled` attribute will provide you a disabled look.

  = code_sample do
    a.btn disabled="disabled" href="#" default

hr

section
  markdown:
    ## Variants [#](#variants)
    {: #variants}

    You have *five* button variants available to you through these classes:

    {: .pco-demo-list}
    * `btn--primary`
    * `btn--secondary`
    * `btn--success`
    * `btn--danger`
    * `btn--link`

  = code_sample do
    a.btn href="#" default
    a.btn.btn--primary href="#" primary
    a.btn.btn--secondary href="#" secondary
    a.btn.btn--success href="#" success
    a.btn.btn--danger href="#" danger
    a.btn.btn--link href="#" link

hr

section
  markdown:
    ## Outline [#](#outline)
    {: #outline}
  = code_sample do
    a.btn.btn--outline href="#" default
    a.btn.btn--outline.btn--primary href="#" primary
    a.btn.btn--outline.btn--secondary href="#" secondary
    a.btn.btn--outline.btn--success href="#" success
    a.btn.btn--outline.btn--danger href="#" danger
    a.btn.btn--outline.btn--link href="#" link

