section
  markdown:
    ## Groups [#](#groups)
    {: #groups}

    Groups allouw you to cobine many related buttons into a single interface element.

  = code_sample do
    ul.btn-group
      li
        a.btn href="#" One
      li
        a.btn href="#" Two
      li
        a.btn href="#" Three

hr

section
  markdown:
    ## Checkboxes [#](#checkboxes)
    {: #checkboxes}

    In some cases, you want a checkbox to not look like a checkbox. You want it to look like a button with a checked and unchecked state.  Here.

    *You'll need the js in place for adding a `selected` class to the `label` element.*

  = code_sample do
    ul.btn-group
      li
        label.btn.btn--small.btn--checkbox.selected for="cool_checkbox"
          input type="checkbox" name="cool_checkbox" id="cool_checkbox"
          | I am cool
      li
        label.btn.btn--small.btn--checkbox for="uncool_checkbox"
          input type="checkbox" name="uncool_checkbox" id="uncool_checkbox"
          | I am uncool

